              <tr>
                <td></td>
                <td colspan="2" valign="top"><h1 align="center"  id="top">MPR DIVISION (Manpower Planning &amp; Recruitment Division)</h1>
                  <p id="MPR"> The Manpower Planning &amp; Recruitment Division is headed by Dy CAO (MPR) who is also the Liaison Officer for SC/ST/PH and Ex-Servicemen Employees of AFHQ/ISOs. It comprises 04 sections viz CAO/R-1, CAO/R-2, CAO/R-3 and CAO/CP Cell. The Charter of Duties of these sections are as under :-</p>
                  <p>(a) <b>Recruitment &ndash; 1 (CAO/R-1)</b></p>
                  <blockquote>
                    <p>(i) Recruitment for Group `A&rsquo; posts;</p>
                    <p>(ii) Recruitment of Section Officers through Civil Services Exam conducted by UPSC;</p>
                    <p>(iii) Recruitment of Senior Technical Assistant, Data Processing Assistant, Senior Research Officer &amp; other Group `B&rsquo; posts in AFHQ;</p>
                    <p>(iv) Compassionate appointment as per Government policy to dependents of AFHQ employees who died while in service or are retired on medical grounds; </p>
                    <p>(v) Recruitment of Multi Tasking Staff (MTS); and</p>
                    <p>(vi) Processing of filling up of post on deputation in AFHQ as per recruitment rules. </p>
                  </blockquote>
                  <p>(b) <b>Recruitment &ndash; 2 (CAO/R-2)</b></p>
                  <blockquote>
                    <p>(i) Framing, Amendment, Review and Repealing of Recruitment Rules of all posts under the Cadre Controlling Authority of the JS(Trg) &amp; CAO in AFHQ and ISOs; </p>
                    <p>(ii) Encadrement/decadrement of posts;</p>
                    <p>(iii) Re-employment of civilians on superannuation;</p>
                    <p>(iv) Re-verification of character and antecedents of Government employees working in sensitive organizations and positive vetting of officers engaged in work of extra sensitive nature in AFHQ &amp; ISOs excluding Naval Headquarters; and </p>
                    <p>(v) Processing of cases received/initiated by Dy CAO (MPR) as Liaison Officer for SC/ST and Physically Handicapped.</p>
                  </blockquote>
                  <p>(c ) <b>Recruitment &ndash; 3 (CAO/R-3)</b></p>
                  <blockquote>
                    <p>(i) Recruitment of Assistants, Steno `C&rsquo; (Personal Assistant), Steno `D&rsquo; and LDC. Recruitment of Senior Translator, Junior Translator and Data Entry Operator Grade `B&rsquo;;</p>
                    <p>(ii) Filling of other isolated posts through Direct Recruitment/Deputation/Re-Employment and absorption basis; and</p>
                    <p>(iii) Direct Recruitment of Staff Car Driver. </p>
                  </blockquote>
                  <p>(d) <b>Career Planning Cell (CAO/CP Cell)</b></p>
                  <blockquote>
                    <p>(i) Cadre Review of various Cadres in AFHQ/ISOs &amp; other matters relating to career progression of employees;</p>
                    <p>(ii) All work relating to Pay Commission including anomalies, Court cases related thereto, implementation etc; </p>
                    <p>(iii) Revision of pay scales based on Govt. decisions on recommendations of expert bodies, etc; and </p>
                    <p>(iv) Vetting of PE of various organization in AFHQ &amp; ISOs in respect of civilian strength. </p>
                  </blockquote>                </td>
              </tr>
